[30;1m30 | [0m[35mString Types[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m------------[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mLike Linux, Git treats filenames as arbitrary bytestrings. There is no prescribed[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35mencoding for these strings, and although it is fairly common to use UTF-8, any[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35mraw byte strings are supported.[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m24 | [0m[35mabout how it seems to work.[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35mThe normalization is a two-fold process that happens at two moments:[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35m- When reading a file from the index and to the working directory. For example[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m  when doing a ``git clone`` or ``git checkout`` call. We call this process the[0m
